"Abstract Last month, in this continuing series of articles examining the Changing Face of International Cryptography Policy, we considered how United States policy in this field has had a critical influence on the position of many other countries, especially on that of the signatories of the Waasenaar Arrangement. Since the publication of that article, there appears to have been a further and dramatic relaxation in US export policy, but it will nonetheless take some time to properly digest the full significance of the recent announcements by David Aaron, Under Secretary at the Department of Commerce and, so-called, Crypto-Czar."
